  "texts": [
    "Additional details of the experimental setup can be found in Appendix B.",
    "Given each model's set of generated labels, the analysis of a model's interpretability of the maxims is decomposed into evaluating: 1) the accuracy of the model's labels, and 2) the model's implicit prioritization of the submaxims.",
    "To this end, we study the pattern of submaxim violations, that is, which individual submaxim violations tend to be associated with other submaxim violations.",
    "This violation pattern is constructed for each model by subdividing the model's set of labels in multiple (12) splits, where each split extracts the conversations in which the model labeled a given response with a (majority) violation for the corresponding submaxim (with all other submaxim dimensions unconstrained).",
    "Fig. 1 illustrates the violation pattern for llama-3-70b-instruct (see Appendix C for the violation patterns for llama-3-8b-instruct and mixtral-8x7b-instruct-v0.1)."
  ],
